";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Darren Rowse";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5438:"<p>Affiliate marketing is one of the blogger&#8217;s mainstay business models. It&#8217;s simple, and as <a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2012/06/29/blog-business-models-4-affiliate-marketing">Anshul proved when he shared his story</a> earlier today, it works—but it does take effort and commitment.</p>
<p>The first challenge is to understand how the process works, and for that I can point you to no better resource than the four-part series Brian Clark wrote for us. Still current, and pulling no punches, this primer is a great place to start if you&#8217;ve never sold targeted affiliate products before:</p>
<ol>
<li><a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2006/07/11/the-secret-of-product-blogs-that-sell/">The secret of blog products that sell</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2006/07/14/why-this-blog-sells-tons-of-ebooks-and-how-it-can-sell-even-more/">Why this blog sells tons of ebooks and how it can sell even more</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2006/07/21/how-to-sell-niche-products-with-your-blog/">How to sell niche products with your blog</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2006/07/29/you-don’t-need-a-product-of-your-own-to-have-a-successful-product-blog/">You don&#8217;t need a product of your own to have a successful product blog</a></li>
</ol>
<p>Once you&#8217;ve worked through those, try these more specific posts that deal with individual challenges that affiliate bloggers need to master:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2012/04/26/whats-the-best-type-of-affiliate-site-case-study/">What&#8217;s the best type of affiliate site?</a> is Anshul Dayal&#8217;s first post on the blog, and compared two different approaches to this business model. It&#8217;s recommended reading for anyone operating in this space.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2011/09/30/how-to-land-the-best-products-to-review/">How to land the best products to review</a>, by Simon Worrall, includes a form email that you can use to get in touch with companies who offer affiliate products.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2011/10/07/the-ultimate-guide-to-professional-product-review-pitches/">The ultimate guide to professional product review pitches</a> provides more detail on the topic, too.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2011/09/26/how-to-get-more-eyeballs-on-your-affiliate-links/">How to get more eyeballs on your affiliate links</a> explains how to use your audience knowledge to closely target your reviews to specific types of readers on your blog.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2012/02/22/blog-smarter-turn-your-blogging-skills-into-successful-affiliate-promotions/">Turn your blogging skills into successful affiliate promotions</a> looks at the words you use—and how you use them—in posts to call readers to take action on your affiliate offers.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2011/10/04/6-tips-for-dressing-up-your-product-reviews/">6 tips for dressing up your product reviews</a>, by Peter Lawlor, steps you through tactics and techniques you can use to make your reviews of affiliate products really grab readers—it&#8217;s a must-read for anyone writing reviews.</li>
<li>Finally, <a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/2011/09/21/why-bloggers-should-pay-attention-to-the-new-affiliate-tax-laws/">Why bloggers should pay attention to the new affiliate tax laws</a>, by Yasmine Mustafa, will be of interested to Amazon affiliates.</li>
</ul>
<p>Of course, here on ProBlogger we have an <a href="http://www.problogger.net/archives/category/affiliate-programs/">archive dedicated to affiliate marketing</a>, so if you&#8217;re after specific advice or solutions, take a look at the posts there.</p>
<p>What other resources can you add to this list to help those who want to improve their affiliate marketing? Share them with us below.</p>
